imports.value: TokenTree, Ident, Span, Punct, TokenStream, Spacing

defs.docs:
This crate provides the [`quote!`] macro for turning Rust syntax tree data
 structures into tokens of source code.

defs.name: TokenStreamExt
defs.docs: TokenStream extension trait with methods for appending tokens.

defs.name: append_separated
defs.value: fn <I, U> (&mut self, iter: I, op: U) -> ()

defs.name: append_terminated
defs.value: fn <I, U> (&mut self, iter: I, term: U) -> ()

defs.name: fmt
defs.docs: Format this value as an identifier fragment.

defs.name: ToTokens
defs.docs: Types that can be interpolated inside a `quote!` invocation.

defs.name: ext
defs.docs:
Extension traits used by the implementation of `quote!`. These are defined
 in separate traits, rather than as a single trait due to ambiguity issues.

defs.name: RepIteratorExt
defs.docs: Extension trait providing the `quote_into_iter` method on iterators.

defs.name: RepToTokensExt
defs.docs:
Extension trait providing the `quote_into_iter` method for
 non-iterable types. These types interpolate the same value in each
 iteration of the repetition.

defs.name: next
defs.docs:
Pretend to be an iterator for the purposes of `quote_into_iter`.
 This allows repeated calls to `quote_into_iter` to continue
 correctly returning DoesNotHaveIter.

defs.name: RepAsIteratorExt
defs.docs:
Extension trait providing the `quote_into_iter` method for types that
 can be referenced as an iterator.
